1
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:17,400
Hey, girl!

2
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:19,600
What are you doing alone?

3
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:21,440
Wait a moment.

4
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,880
I know you've been down lately.

5
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,800
Let's go have some hotpot. My treat.

6
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,320
Let's go...

7
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,120
We all

8
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:32,880
know your dad got arrested.

9
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,240
So drop the act.

10
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,960
Stop acting like a princess.

11
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:37,360
Move aside.

12
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:38,640
I'm curious, though.

13
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,920
Why did your dad get arrested?

14
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:42,880
Murder?

15
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,160
Robbery?

16
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,080
Or running this kind of shop?

17
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,160
Say one more word about my dad,

18
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:50,520
and I'll mess you up, got it?

19
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,040
No one's protecting her. Get her.

20
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:53,600
Listen,

21
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:56,040
your dad's already in jail.

22
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,760
You've got no one to back you up now.

23
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:00,920
You should feel lucky I even fancy you.

24
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:02,400
Don't push your luck.

25
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:03,800
Let me tell you,

26
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,400
you're eating this meal,

27
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,280
whether you like it or not, understand?

28
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,640
Back when my dad was around,

29
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,520
you didn't dare say a word.

30
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:18,040
Even if my dad did wrong,

31
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:21,000
he's still better than cowards like you.

32
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Your dad's in jail now.

33
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:29,480
Not sure if he'll ever get out.

34
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,080
You better drop
your princess attitude, got it?

35
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,520
Hold her.

36
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,960
Why is it you again?

37
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:04,840
Mr. Lin,

38
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:07,080
you recovered from your injury?

39
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,720
What's wrong?

40
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,000
Nothing.

41
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,240
Do me a favor.

42
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,040
Stay away from her.

43
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:19,720
Alright.

44
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,440
I'm doing it for your sake.

45
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,240
Just this once.

46
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:25,560
Let's go.

47
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,200
Next time, use your eyes.

48
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:44,720
Are you alright?

49
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,560
Why is it that my dad's in jail,

50
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,720
Mr. Qin is dead,

51
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,560
but you're still fine?

52
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,320
Why do you get to be innocent

53
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,280
without getting involved?

54
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,120
You can blame me

55
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,200
or hate me,

56
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,200
but think about Uncle Erjin.

57
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,440
If he knew you were living like this,

58
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,440
how worried he'd be.

59
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,200
Let me walk you home.

60
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,040
I don't need you
playing the good guy here.

61
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,280
Get lost.

62
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,000
Get lost!

63
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:25,140
[Producer Zhang Yimou]

64
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:54,980
[The First Shot]

65
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,900
[Episode 20]

66
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,720
You need to get some good sleep tonight.

67
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,720
So tired.

68
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:03,040
I'll bring breakfast over tomorrow.

69
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,280
Been trailing pusher for so long,

70
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:08,400
I've worn out two pairs of socks,

71
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:10,000
and there's still no progress.

72
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,680
When will we ever catch the big fish?

73
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:12,600
What's the rush?

74
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,000
No case is easy to crack.

75
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:15,960
Hold on.

76
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:20,840
I have an idea.

77
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:25,880
We've been

78
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,960
tracing the retail level upward.

79
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,600
But there's been no breakthrough.

80
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,400
I thought about it.

81
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,200
What if we flip it around?

82
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:35,000
Work from the top down.

83
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,040
What do you mean?

84
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,880
From the top down?

85
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:41,000
You mean
starting with drug manufacturing?

86
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:43,360
We can't even confirm Mr. Ma's identity,

87
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,760
let alone find where the drug was made.

88
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,800
No.

89
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:50,120
Drug production is just
the middle of the chain.

90
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,160
The real source is
in the chemical raw materials.

91
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,800
Don't forget,

92
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,320
today's meth

93
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,960
is chemically processed.

94
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,440
Unlike before, when it was grown.

95
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,680
That's a good approach.

96
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,360
We have the Lucifer's recipe,

97
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,080
so we can trace back the raw materials.

98
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,400
How do you plan to investigate?

99
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,640
Think about it,

100
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,360
the raw materials for making meth

101
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,640
are mostly controlled substances.

102
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:19,120
Except for chemical plants
or drug companies,

103
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,920
ordinary people
can hardly get access to them.

104
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,920
Factory profits and losses
are on record.

105
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,400
If we just go there for data,

106
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,560
we might tip them off.

107
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,320
But we could go to the banks

108
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,840
to apply for their financial records.

109
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,040
Going to the bank?

110
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,040
Let me put it simply.

111
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,360
If a factory

112
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,560
supplies raw materials

113
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,120
to drug dealers,

114
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,160
its actual production will be way lower

115
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,640
than what it should be.

116
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,080
But the purchasing
and sales amounts should match.

117
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,400
These will be reflected

118
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,800
in their financial records.

119
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:59,400
So, those with high costs
and low income,

120
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:01,560
and timelines matching the appearance

121
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:03,440
of Lucifer

122
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,760
are our key suspects.

123
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,080
Alright,

124
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,040
starting tomorrow,

125
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,000
we'll split up the work.

126
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:09,520
Xueyao and Xiaoguang,

127
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:11,480
follow me to check on the pusher.

128
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,000
Guozhu, you follow Mr. Gu

129
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,080
to investigate the factories.

130
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,800
So let's get a good rest tonight.

131
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,320
Got it.

132
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,280
Tomorrow,
we begin strict investigations.

133
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:18,440
Okay.

134
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,160
Go home now.

135
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,400
- See you tomorrow, Ran.
- See you tomorrow.

136
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,080
Don't forget the breakfast, Bei.

137
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,480
Zhao Xiaoguang!

138
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,320
Nan?

139
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:30,280
Hey,

140
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,840
what are you two doing here?

141
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,080
What are you doing here so late?

142
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:36,360
I...

143
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:39,280
I borrowed some movies to watch.

144
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,200
What's up?

145
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,120
Why now? It's late.

146
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,840
You should go back.

147
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,440
Watch it tomorrow.

148
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,800
We're watching something else.

149
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,680
What are you watching?

150
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:53,840
Relaxing with a crime movie?

151
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,480
Just looking for some inspiration.

152
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,600
Have a seat.

153
00:08:59,040 --> 00:08:59,840
Sit down.

154
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,520
Why don't you sit over there?

155
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,080
It's crowded there.

156
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:23,880
Besides, this spot is fine.

157
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,600
True.

158
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,080
I forgot your eyesight isn't great.

159
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,880
Your eyes are the ones
that aren't great.

160
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:34,320
If you find me annoying, I'll leave.

161
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,080
No!

162
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,720
That's not what I meant.

163
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,000
What's wrong with you today?

164
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,560
Who got under your skin?

165
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,160
Mid-Autumn Festival is coming.

166
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,640
Your parents are coming back.

167
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,120
Help me pick out some gifts.

168
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,400
They always bring me stuff.

169
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,720
I want to show my appreciation.

170
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:28,920
By the way,

171
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,560
there are some new tapes
at the Video Hall.

172
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:34,240
Let's pick some out together later.

173
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,480
Sure, no problem.

174
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:44,880
Why are you so quiet today?

175
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,840
Ran doesn't like people talking

176
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,720
during a movie.

177
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:53,920
He'll get so mad.

178
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,280
My brother is such a pain.

179
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,240
So is that Mr. Gu.

180
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,080
He doesn't say a word

181
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,680
during a movie.

182
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,200
Who watches a movie without chatting

183
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,400
or having snacks?

184
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,160
Zhao Xiaoguang is right.

185
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:26,600
We're not even on the same wavelength.

186
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:31,640
So you've moved on so quickly?

187
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,760
It's frustrating to even think about it.

188
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,720
I've been trying to find a way

189
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,440
to spend some alone time

190
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,480
with Zhao Xiaoguang,

191
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,040
but every time,

192
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:45,280
he's busy with work,

193
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,320
or

194
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,480
my annoying brother

195
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,800
is hanging around.

196
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,200
What should I do?

197
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,880
Any ideas?

198
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,640
Well,

199
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,040
we girls can't just confess.

200
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,040
He likes you, anyway.

201
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,480
Just seduce him.

202
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,080
Let him know you like him too.

203
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,200
Seduce?

204
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:18,720
I can punch,

205
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,800
but seducing...

206
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,440
I...

207
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,480
I can't do that.

208
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,320
Oh my, don't be a coward.

209
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:28,680
Just say something suggestive.

210
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,400
If that doesn't work,

211
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,800
make a move.

212
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,160
You learned nothing
from all those romance movies?

213
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,400
Why are all your movies romances?

214
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:58,960
Are you dating someone?

215
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:00,320
No.

216
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:02,720
I'm just studying ahead of time.

217
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,080
I used to like Joker

218
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,320
from A Chinese Odyssey.

219
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:12,160
Then I liked Qiao Feng
from Demi-Gods and Semi-Devils.

220
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:13,960
Recently, I watched Emergency Unit.

221
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,640
I find Chen Xiaochun is handsome too.

222
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,600
Doesn't matter
if he's the main character or not,

223
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,080
as long as he's a police,

224
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:26,000
he just seems reliable.

225
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,320
So I'm just saying

226
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,440
I'm fickle.

227
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:38,200
I could just like anyone.

228
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:43,520
You...

229
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:46,160
You get what I'm saying?

230
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,760
You could like anyone,

231
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,760
but it can't be me.

232
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,720
How could I miss

233
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,320
such an obvious hint?

234
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,000
I get it.

235
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,800
I better hurry up

236
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:03,320
and spend more time with you

237
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,080
before your prince charming shows up.

238
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,120
Once you're with someone,

239
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,200
I'll step back.

240
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,240
No, I...

241
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,080
Please, stop.

242
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,480
I understand.

243
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,520
You fool!

244
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,080
Who is it?

245
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:31,800
Xiaohai, open the door.

246
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,800
What's with the big bags?

247
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,720
Why are you here at this time?

248
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,360
I've been swamped at work.

249
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:43,880
I'm only available now.

250
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:46,920
Have you eaten?

251
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,880
Yes.

252
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,000
I just got paid today.

253
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,120
I had a big dinner.

254
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:50,840
Really?

255
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,440
Let me look at your fridge.

256
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:54,840
It's all beer

257
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:55,920
and nothing else.

258
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,680
These are chicken ribs and sausage.

259
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,040
Put them in the freezer.

260
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,800
Heat them up whenever you're hungry.

261
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,040
These are dumplings my mom made.

262
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,840
This one's pork and sauerkraut filling.

263
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,280
This one's beef and scallion filling.

264
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,480
Thanks, Bei.

265
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,560
Make sure you eat them.

266
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:13,600
Don't worry.

267
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,840
I'll finish them in three days.

268
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,320
You can come check
if you don't believe me.

269
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:17,920
Why?

270
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,280
You're such a grown-up.

271
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,440
Hey, get me some scissors,

272
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,440
will you?

273
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:25,480
Sure, just a second.

274
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:29,880
Okay.

275
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,040
What is this?

276
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:35,680
A fan.

277
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:37,560
How's your work

278
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,000
at the skating rink now?

279
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:40,960
Pretty good.

280
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,000
The boss treats me well.

281
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,240
But there's no room for growth

282
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:46,800
working there.

283
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:47,640
Maybe you can

284
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,600
start your own business?

285
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,840
I've thought about it,

286
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:56,200
but I haven't decided what to do yet.

287
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:57,880
I'll keep thinking about it.

288
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,200
Okay.

289
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,440
Your sister runs a pharmacy, right?

290
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:03,840
She's got business experience.

